spanGrp.span: They were shut far in the mountain, the sheep were.
Jie-wa ts estee kte-l-wa kom montaa jrga ska obeja-wa ts kte-l-wa (_)
A car carrying fruits goes by and [the fruits] fell down.
Pe karro k-ge-w kalw dam jargs'
There they began to play; they just played.
jeska jie-wa dw-g-w jin jin Jie-wa jin-g wakwa b
The pigs were locked in and saw how the others were playing;
jeska kuchi yabla ts kte-l-wa ts jie-wa s' mnbi jie-wa jin-g bi
they wantes to play with the fruit; they played a lot.
Jie-wa jin-gle kalw wa jie-wa jino-g t'
The little pigs also wanted to play;
they could not/they were locked in and thus could not play with the others.
(_) jie-wa ka / (_) jie-wa jie-wa ts kte-l-wa ka jinr jie-wa ra
At that point, they helped. The were happy how to play with the comrades.
Je_juetara jie-wa kime-g jie-wa jie-wa ksr-g-n mnbi siga-wa jin-g je wa
Then they burst the house with that fruit.
Kea jie-wa t pe j j kw'-w (_) je kalw wa
Thus the man locked them in and they got sad.
Je kueinga pekaga t jie-wa ktie-g-w je wa (_) pekaga t jie-wa ktie-g-w ska jie-wa jr ian'-w
They wanted to play; the little pigs became sad.
Jie-wa jin-gle kuchi yabla jr ian'-w
Then they went to play; they played.
Tgapa jie-wa m-geu-lo-n jin jeska jin-g
kea pato yabla ts ksr-g-ka jiebi
The ducks saw how the pigs were playing and they became happy.
jie-wa s-g-ite mn jie-wa jin-g bi pato yabla ksr-g-ka
Jeme jie-wa jie-wa jie-wa r-g-w todo
jie-wa ksr-g-ka klabe mn jie-wa jin bi
They wanted to keep playing but there were no more fruits to play with.
Jie-wa jie-wa jin-gle pero ka ka kalw ta jie-wa jin-gl
They were locked in really far but they were all happy.
Jie-wa ts kte-l-wa kom' pe-wa jeska jie-wa jie-wa jin-g jie-wa ksr-g-ka klabe ara r
They went to hide from the people behind the trees.
Jebi jie-wa jie-wa m-geu-lo m pe-wa kal kate ska bl pe yiga
The people saw them break the window, so they went to hide;
Pe t jie-wa s' jie-wa t pe bidrio kw'-w jeska jie-wa m-ge-ulo bl
so the people were going to lock them in; they got sad because they wanted to keep playing.
Tgapa jie-wa pe t ktie-g-w ska jie-wa jr ian'-w jie-wa jin-gle-n
There they were playing together and were happy till the end.
